  "text": "Although qualitative research is unfamiliar to most quantitatively oriented physicians, it is a powerful tool for gaining insight into patient perspectives and answering questions that cannot be answered by quantitative research methodology [CITATION_1] . Qualitative findings are not generalizable; rather, they are indicative of a range of common experiences.",
